Wildfire Aesthetics

Brenna Kelly

11/3/2021

The Problem. Currently, the official maps of active wildfires and projects in Utah leave to be desired. All wildfire, whether 1 acre or 1000, have the same visual representation on the map a fire icon. For fires that are no longer active (100% containment), the icon is converted to grayscale. Additionally, in order to find the percent containment, you need to click on the icon. At a glance, theres not much information about the individual fires.

I think we can do better.

Data. I created a practice dataframe containing size (in acres), percent containment, latitude, and longitude for 10 fires in Utah.

#example df
size <- c(80, 100, 60, 350, 200, 115, 150, 210, 65, 250)
containment <- c(.15, 0.50, 0.90, 0.25, 0.45, 0.25, 0.75, 0.35, 0.3, 0.75)
latitude <- c(39.310891, 39.958603, 39.409207, 39.137349, 37.955561, 40.545617, 41.462945, 37.647802, 40.768892, 40.829682)
longitude <- c(-109.686827, -109.845825, -110.257095, -111.578108, -111.800678, -110.541577, -111.548056, -109.857025, -111.692851, -111.262928)

fires <- data.frame(size, containment, latitude, longitude)

Visualization. The new fire icons visually represent:

  1. Location of the fire you can see latitude and longitude with the grids.
  2. Acres burned the size of the fire corresponds to the circle diameter.
  3. Percent containment the color is
myPal <- colorRampPalette((brewer.pal(11, "RdYlGn")))

fire <- ggplot(data = fires, aes(x = longitude, y = latitude, colour = containment)) +
  geom_point(aes(size = size), alpha = 0.90) +
  scale_size_continuous(range = c(10, 30)) +
  scale_colour_gradientn(colours = myPal(100), limits = c(0, 1)) +
  geom_point(data = fires, colour = "gray15", aes(size = (size*3)/5), alpha = 0.70) +
  geom_text(aes(label = containment)) +
  xlim(-113, -109) +
  ylim(37, 42) +
  xlab("Longitude") +
  ylab("Latitude") +
  ggtitle("Fires in Utah: Acreage and Containment") +
  theme_minimal()

fire + labs(size = "Acreage", colour = "Percent Containment")
